    "narrative": "The Sunday slate for LawDog is anchored by **Cal Raleigh**, who commands the highest score of the day at 78.02. His matchup against Prielipp is the clear highlight, as **Cal Raleigh** benefits from a strong SP_xERA of 4.50 and a favorable park factor, compounded by an aggressive #2 spot in the order. **Will Smith** follows closely at 72.25, capitalizing on a weak matchup against Chris Paddack; with the wind blowing out, **Will Smith** is positioned to provide elite production from the heart of the lineup. Meanwhile, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** remains a must-start at 66.83; despite a marginal grade on the opposing arm, his plate discipline and spot in the #3 hole keep his floor remarkably high regardless of the platoon disadvantage against Matz.\n\nThe secondary tier of our lineup reveals the volatility of today\u2019s matchups. **Jonathan Aranda** (43.51) and **Masyn Winn** (41.44) both hover dangerously close to the \"Below floor\" threshold. **Jonathan Aranda** faces a stiff challenge against Messick, and while his order placement saves his value, the negative adjustments for the SP skill leave little room for error. **Masyn Winn** is similarly squeezed, hampered by a negative wind factor and a tough matchup against Montgomery, M. While we are keeping **Lawrence Butler**, **Geraldo Perdomo**, **Yainer Diaz**, and **Tyler Freeman** on the bench due to team off-days, our remaining depth\u2014including **Bryson Stott**, **Taylor Ward**, **Matt Chapman**, **Daulton Varsho**, **Luis Arraez**, **Jeremiah Jackson**, **Brendan Donovan**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, **Gleyber Torres**, **Wenceel Perez**, **Gavin Sheets**, and **Drew Gilbert**\u2014remains ready to rotate in as scheduling permits. No player on the active roster was benched by choice today; the optimization was dictated strictly by the lack of games for our reserve corps, meaning the active starters must carry the load to preserve our valuable game caps.",
